= Basic Operation =

== GPlates Screenshots ==

=== Main Window ===

image:screenshot1.png[]

`---------------------------`-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Application  		      Description
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Menu Bar (2)		      The region of the main window which contains the titles of the menus.
Tool Palette (3)	      A collection of tools which are used to interact with the globe and features in the Globe View via the mouse pointer. The tools in the toolbox include "Drag globe to re-orient" and "Click geometry".	
Task Panel (4)		      Task specific information and controls, that corresponds to the current tool
Reconstruction View (5)	      The region of the main window which contains the Globe View, Time Controls, Zoom Controls, Zoom Slider, Camera Coordinates and Mouse Coordinates. 
Clicked Geometry Table (6)    Displays a summary of each geometry or feature touched by the lsat mouse click.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

=== Main Window with View Menu ===

image:screenshot2.png[]
`-----------------------------`----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Application  		         Description
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Menu (1) 		         A collection of menu items, each of which performs a single operation. 
Menu Bar (2)		         The region of the main window which contains the titles of the menus.
Tool Palette (3)	         A collection of tools which are used to interact with the globe and features in the Globe View via the mouse pointer. 
